      "text": [
        " إِذَا كَانَ الْبَيْتُ فَوْقَ ثَمَانِيَةِ أَذْرُعٍ فَاكْتُبْ فِي أَعْلَاهُ آيَةَ الْكُرْسِيِّ ."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "From him, from Ali Bin Al Hakam, and Muhsan Bin Ahmad, from Aban Bin Usman, form Muhammad Bin Ismail, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having said: ‘When the house is above eight cubits, so write in its upper part the Verse of the Chair <a href=\"/#/books/quran:2#h255\">[2:255]</a>’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "7. It is narrated from the narrator of the previous Hadith Ali ibn al-Hakam and Muhassan ibn Ahmad from Aban ibn ‘Uthman from Muhammad ibn ’Isma‘il who has said the following: “Abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, has said, ‘If the height of the house is more than eight yards (Zira’ arm-length) then write verse 2:255 above that level.’” "
        ]
      }
    }
